Input.user: Another question I have is, what original documents do I require?
Input.gold: you also must show us your I-20 Certificate of Eligibility for Nonimmigrant Student Status
Input.baseline: We can accept only certain documents as proof of U.S. citizenship. These include a U.S. birth certificate or a U.S. passport.

To replace your child's Social Security card, you will need to provide proof of your child's U.S. citizenship and identity. Since your child was not born on American soil, you will need to provide proof of U.S. citizenship. Acceptable documents for proof of U.S. citizenship include Certification of Report of Birth DS-1350, Consular Report of Birth Abroad FS-240 or CRBA, U.S. passport, or Certificate of Citizenship N-560/N-561.

For proof of your child's identity, we prefer to see the child's U.S. passport. If that document is not available, we may accept other documents such as a state-issued non-driver's identification card, adoption decree, doctor, clinic or hospital record, religious record, school daycare center record, or school identification card.

Additionally, we will need proof of your identity as well. An acceptable document must be current and not expired. If you have any further questions or need more information, please let me know.
Input.reaction: You will need to provide a state-issued non-driver's identification card, adoption decree, doctor, clinic or hospital record, religious record, school daycare center record, or school identification card as proof of your child's identity. As for proof of your own identity, you will need to provide a current and not expired document.
